{
  "name": "whittle",
  "description": "A sunlit wooden desk that learned to sing. Warm felt taps and knuckle knocks under a clear little woodblock \u2014 the tactile working sounds you already love \u2014 now answered by a singing kalimba-mallet, sweet celeste chimes, a breathing sub-bass floor, a soft maternal bloom, a glowing pentatonic welcome, and a happy little bird. A major pentatonic, additive and clean, Boards-of-Canada warm. Every register is covered: the wood keeps the room in-the-room and dry, the melodic voices float bright over it, and the bass grounds it all without ever turning dark, busy, or harsh.",
